Package com.bmd.jrt.annotation

Annotation definitions.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DefaultLog
    Log interface used to identify the default log instance in a Async annotation.
    DefaultRunner
    Runner interface used to identify the default runner in a Async annotation.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Async
    This annotation is used to indicate methods that are to be invoked in an asynchronous way.
    AsyncClass
    This annotation is used to indicate interfaces used as templates to generate wrapper classes enabling asynchronous calls to the target instance methods.
    AsyncType
    This annotation is used to indicate methods whose parameters or output are passed asynchronously.
    ParallelType
    This annotation is used to indicate methods whose parameters or output are passed asynchronously.
